36:06.941 --> 36:09.559
♪ oh, cool water

36:09.611 --> 36:12.562
♪ yeah, and that cool wind

36:12.614 --> 36:14.281
watches in the bag.
Watches in the bag.

36:14.365 --> 36:16.399
I know you got a watch.
Don't give me that.

36:16.451 --> 36:19.920
You know, man it smell
like Yankee in here, don't it?

36:20.004 --> 36:21.738
Ma'am, I need you to put
that purse in this bag.

36:21.789 --> 36:25.408
Take the ring off your finger!

36:25.460 --> 36:26.760
Hurry up!

36:26.844 --> 36:28.011
I'm gonna put a hole
in your boy's head

36:28.079 --> 36:30.347
if you don't give me that ring.

36:30.414 --> 36:31.715
Hurry up!

36:31.766 --> 36:33.884
Hurry up! Try harder!

36:33.935 --> 36:35.936
You want a dead child
in your lap?

36:36.020 --> 36:38.222
I will kill this Yankee spawn.

36:38.273 --> 36:40.057
Take that ring off your finger!

36:40.108 --> 36:41.591
Get that ring off your finger!

36:41.643 --> 36:43.110
Do you want this boy to die?!

36:43.194 --> 36:45.529
You better stand down, son.

36:45.596 --> 36:47.931
Last chance.

36:49.934 --> 36:53.120
No. It's yours.

37:04.448 --> 37:05.966
Hey.

37:06.050 --> 37:07.784
Shit.

37:15.265 --> 37:17.283
They're watching us.

37:18.985 --> 37:21.036
I can feel it.

37:22.889 --> 37:24.408
After what happened
to you and Robert,

37:24.528 --> 37:28.244
I can understand your unease.

37:28.295 --> 37:30.731
We surveyed this area.

37:30.851 --> 37:33.731
The Sioux believe the land
across that river

37:33.851 --> 37:34.981
is sacred...

37:36.266 --> 37:38.807
Where the earth touches heaven.

37:40.390 --> 37:44.593
Robert wanted to avoid it.

37:44.644 --> 37:48.264
What do you think?

37:48.315 --> 37:53.819
My husband was rarely wrong
on these matters.

37:53.904 --> 37:57.656
I know they're over there
waiting for us.

37:57.741 --> 37:59.474
We can't ignore them.

37:59.526 --> 38:02.328
But they will be
the least of our troubles

38:02.412 --> 38:05.698
if we don't get
this railroad under control.

38:21.166 --> 38:23.464
Unless you got a bee
in your throat,

38:23.584 --> 38:27.002
best cease that hum sound.

38:29.773 --> 38:32.775
A happy man's got a right
to hum, all right?

38:32.842 --> 38:37.062
Son, you're getting set
to be hanged.

38:38.481 --> 38:43.152
Nah, they won't hang me.

38:43.203 --> 38:45.788
Shoot me, most likely.

38:53.863 --> 38:55.197
Ha ha ha ha ha!

38:55.248 --> 38:58.200
♪ Take me home
to the land of cotton ♪

38:58.251 --> 39:01.637
♪ old times there
are not forgotten ♪

39:01.704 --> 39:05.174
♪ look away, look away

39:05.225 --> 39:06.981
♪ look away...

39:07.101 --> 39:08.715
♪ Dixieland

39:12.215 --> 39:14.717
Shut up.

39:24.094 --> 39:26.512
I don't...

39:26.596 --> 39:29.648
I don't know what to say
about this.

39:29.733 --> 39:33.068
Whore. Hmm?

39:34.988 --> 39:40.242
Well, it was a whore who...

39:40.310 --> 39:45.247
Bathed the feet of Jesus
with--with her hair.

39:46.866 --> 39:49.368
Yeah. Amen.

39:56.126 --> 39:58.160
Huh?

40:01.765 --> 40:03.665
Yah.

40:03.717 --> 40:06.685
Uh...

40:08.838 --> 40:14.310
Father, accept this whore
into the ground

40:14.361 --> 40:17.780
so that her corruption
may be completed.

40:17.847 --> 40:21.784
May her soul
be eternally forgotten.

40:21.851 --> 40:28.190
May we be cleansed
of her memory.

40:28.258 --> 40:30.367
Yah.

40:30.487 --> 40:34.880
These things in your name.
Humbly.

40:37.083 --> 40:39.218
Amen.

40:39.302 --> 40:42.371
Amen.

40:44.257 --> 40:47.209
Dig! Dig.

40:47.260 --> 40:48.644
New graves, sir.

40:48.711 --> 40:53.015
Many new graves.

40:53.066 --> 40:54.817
We shall plant our--

40:54.884 --> 40:58.854
our strange crop,

40:58.905 --> 41:01.023
and the lord...

41:01.074 --> 41:02.825
The lord...

41:02.892 --> 41:08.230
will pour forth
his bounty upon us.

42:09.792 --> 42:12.561
Hey, Johnny Reb!

42:14.180 --> 42:17.632
Time to wake up!

42:17.684 --> 42:20.602
You better start
singin' "Dixie."

42:20.653 --> 42:23.572
'Cause you're next!

42:25.575 --> 42:27.743
Aim...

42:27.810 --> 42:29.495
Fire!

42:29.579 --> 42:30.913
Aah!

